Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,==============================================MAIN==================================================
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.76,0:00:21.38,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1124,995)}ἐκκλησία
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.76,0:00:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, the Soul Church will
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.38,0:00:26.25,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1072,1000)}απάθεια
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.38,0:00:26.25,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1650,1000)}όρκα
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.38,0:00:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,hold an inquisition on the former apatheia corps commander, Orca.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.98,0:00:30.30,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1410,1000)}φάλαινα
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.98,0:00:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Although we have to keep the sinners of Fallaina,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.94,0:00:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,who has been exiled to the great sea of sand, from being found by
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.62,0:00:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the United Kingdom of Sidelasia and other countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.87,0:00:41.37,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(708,1000)}φάλαινα
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.87,0:00:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But Fallaina is in exile at the evil water.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.69,0:00:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be extremely difficult to approach and even discover them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.37,0:00:46.71,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1174,1000)}φάλαινα
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.37,0:00:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The annihilation of Fallaina,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.71,0:00:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,was not an action that we have to take at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.62,0:00:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Who proposed and forced us to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.62,0:00:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.76,0:00:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, the exile judged 93 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.18,0:01:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,was a {\i1}story{\i0} for our citizens to take it as an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.64,0:01:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,By the story that the sinners revealed their {\i1}emotions{\i0} and conflicted ugly,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.15,0:01:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,our citizens can recognize the foolishness of having emotions again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.73,0:01:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how you persuaded his Majesty as well as us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.78,0:01:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,However, your strategy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.78,0:01:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.41,0:01:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,At his Majesty's command,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.00,0:01:29.70,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(322,1000)}απάθεια
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.00,0:01:29.70,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(888,1000)}όρκα
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.00,0:01:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,apatheia corps commander Orca, the chief executive of this action,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.04,0:01:32.60,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1278,1000)}σκύλος
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.04,0:01:32.60,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(666,1000)}αράχνη
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.04,0:01:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Arakhne, the commander of skulax,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.60,0:01:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as other hundreds of people are sentenced to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.49,0:01:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.05,0:01:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the best {\i1}story{\i0} you may tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.95,0:01:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.31,0:01:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.81,0:01:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I just... thought it was a little shabby.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.03,0:01:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.94,0:01:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep from responding to his provocation!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.82,0:01:58.92,Default,,0,60,0,,{\an3}Long long ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.61,0:02:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The heaven cut a piece of its body,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.95,0:02:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and gave it to the world it has once rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.31,0:02:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, the old bad civilization had faced its death and rebirth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.61,0:02:13.53,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1300,1000)}καθαρτήριο
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.61,0:02:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the tale of {\i1}the rain of purgatory
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.13,0:02:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.63,0:02:24.76,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1312,995)}νοῦς
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.63,0:02:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,After the world had been cleaned up, we worshiped Nous, the body of heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.81,0:02:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We got its power.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.35,0:02:31.26,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1744,995)}νοῦς
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.35,0:02:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And we determined to deposit our minds, the roots of our faults, with Nous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.90,0:02:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we have two types of human beings in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.72,0:02:41.14,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(772,995)}νοῦς
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.72,0:02:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The evangelists of Nous, and those who can't be evangelists.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.72,0:02:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Evangelists are called {\i1}Shirushi{\i0}, and those who can't are {\i1}Muin{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.33,0:02:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now let's talk about something you may have already forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.53,0:02:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a third type of human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.80,0:02:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The third...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.75,0:02:58.12,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1084,995)}δαίμονας
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.75,0:02:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the Daímonas
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.13,0:03:02.66,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1150,995)}νοῦς
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.13,0:03:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate warrior created by Nous with its power.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.26,0:03:05.49,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(788,1000)}δαίμονας
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.26,0:03:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Daímonas is just a rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.14,0:03:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how we forgot these, treating them as the bygones.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.69,0:03:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we can't pretend as they are not existing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.09,0:03:16.64,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1346,1000)}σκύλος
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.09,0:03:16.64,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(832,1000)}φάλαινα
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.09,0:03:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The boy in Fallaina who destroyed Skulax,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.38,0:03:18.95,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1140,995)}δαίμονας
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.38,0:03:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,he is exactly the Daímonas!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.11,0:03:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me redifine it here:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.96,0:03:26.15,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(622,1000)}δαίμονας
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.96,0:03:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Daímonas is the threat that came back to our empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.33,0:03:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They have the power to overturn our country, which should be an ark.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.65,0:03:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They are the recognition of some terrible sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.70,0:03:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,After you have seen such an existence...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.28,0:03:38.17,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,1000)}αράχνη
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.28,0:03:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Arakhne!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.30,0:03:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you treat him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.71,0:03:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the records, you despised and abused him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.21,0:03:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And you even provoked him!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.25,0:03:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.98,0:03:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't say you are innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.27,0:03:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I can even say you are badly...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.64,0:03:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.33,0:04:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No... no!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.57,0:04:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Orca pulled his weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.47,0:04:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.00,0:04:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The records are full of blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.50,0:04:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Who had assigned missions to such a guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.55,0:04:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,who can't even control his emotions?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.80,0:04:26.90,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(996,995)}ἐκκλησία
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.80,0:04:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.39,0:04:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Even you have never been to the battle field,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.39,0:04:33.06,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1332,995)}νοῦς
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.39,0:04:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,don't forget it's your fault to have thee Nous sank.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.94,0:04:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's turn to the {\i1}new chapter{\i0} of our story.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.47,0:04:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You say the {\i1}new chapter?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.17,0:04:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It is quite possible that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.48,0:04:45.68,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(852,1000)\i1}καθαρτήριο
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.48,0:04:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a {\i1}second rain of purgatory{\i0} will fall in the near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.71,0:04:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't change the topic!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.40,0:04:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare you live without even a single sense of crisis!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.48,0:04:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This world can't be clean unless it is washed and cleaned again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.95,0:04:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that time we must protect this country,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.40,0:05:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which will become an ark.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.05,0:05:05.43,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(556,995)}δαίμονας
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.05,0:05:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Daímonas should be controlled by our country.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.76,0:05:07.72,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1320,1000)}δαίμονας
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.76,0:05:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you want to control the Daímonas?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.05,0:05:10.74,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1372,1000)}φάλαινα
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.05,0:05:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We can just destroy it along with the Fallaina.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.47,0:05:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Who can?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.89,0:05:15.52,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1300,1000)}δαίμονας
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.89,0:05:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Who do you think can kill the Daímonas?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.27,0:05:22.00,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(958,1000)}δαίμονας
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.27,0:05:22.00,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1450,1000)}νοῦς
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.27,0:05:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you mean if the Daímonas sinks another Nous,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.40,0:05:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you will just execute those who involved?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And make it as if nothing happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.57,0:05:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.00,0:05:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brains are just like the ruins under the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.29,0:05:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,badly corroded with rust!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.30,0:05:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Take your story of devastation!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.24,0:05:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you do in this situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.29,0:05:43.19,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1070,1000)}δαίμονας
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.29,0:05:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I will capture the Daímonas for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.63,0:05:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Only I can make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.51,0:05:53.35,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(592,1000)}δαίμονας
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.51,0:05:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Daímonas rewrited the theory of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.90,0:05:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence of it will lead our country to the absolute hegemon of the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.65,0:05:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.86,0:06:08.24,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1308,1000)}δαίμονας
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.86,0:06:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I did well until the discovery of Daímonas.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.16,0:06:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There is only one thing I have to regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.41,0:06:14.52,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1264,1000)}σκύλος
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.41,0:06:14.52,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(988,1000)}αράχνη
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.41,0:06:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the arbitrariness of Arakhne the Skulax commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.56,0:06:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.87,0:06:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. We leave him to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.04,0:06:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait... Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.42,0:06:22.25,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1070,1000)}όρκα
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.42,0:06:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You dare! Orca!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.08,0:06:24.98,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(944,1000)}όρκα
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.08,0:06:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Orca!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.55,0:06:28.54,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1294,995)}νοῦς
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.55,0:06:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Heaven blesses the servants of Nous!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.20,0:06:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.53,0:06:52.04,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(554,1000)}ατσάλι
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.53,0:06:52.04,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1334,1000)}απάθεια
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.53,0:06:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear Atsali, our current commander of apatheia corps
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.37,0:06:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The finish of inquisition
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.12,0:06:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean your failure has been canceled out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.79,0:07:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.37,0:07:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is no point in pulling your leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.96,0:07:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me tell you straight away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.88,0:07:11.07,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1218,1000)}καρχαρίας
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.88,0:07:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me the battleship Karcharías.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.72,0:07:14.45,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1208,1000)}σκύλος
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.72,0:07:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have just lost Skulax.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.10,0:07:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you agreed to give it to me, the church will accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.09,0:07:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.57,0:07:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember the first time you talked with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.19,0:07:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.08,0:07:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to give it to me immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.41,0:07:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have some days to think it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.45,0:07:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm waiting for your good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.71,0:07:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.17,0:07:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Something about the dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.64,0:07:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You {\i1}Shirushi{\i0} have had a same dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.34,0:07:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.76,0:08:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In that dream, a girl entered our ears and sang a song.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.56,0:08:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What did... it imply?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.77,0:08:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And after all, for us Muin who didn't have that dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.28,0:08:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,it is difficult to get over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.20,0:08:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.70,0:08:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We understand it, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.62,0:08:34.75,IMJP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}♪　ラララ…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.64,0:08:51.28,IMJP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}♪　ラララ…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.12,0:08:59.18,IMJP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}♪　私たちを
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.08,0:09:05.93,IMJP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}♪　見つけておくれ
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.28,0:09:13.32,IMJP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}♪　泥の船で櫂を漕ぎ
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.70,0:09:22.14,IMJP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}♪　白砂の褥で眠る
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.47,0:09:28.50,IMJP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}♪　小さな旅人よ
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.68,0:09:40.60,IMJP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}♪　ただひとつになろうとしても
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.78,0:09:57.36,IMJP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}♪　無限のちらばりにしかなれない
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.62,0:08:34.75,IMEN,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}Lalala...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.64,0:08:51.28,IMEN,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}Lalala...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.12,0:08:59.18,IMEN,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}Please find us
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.08,0:09:05.93,IMEN,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}in the sea of sand
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.28,0:09:13.32,IMEN,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}Rowing the paddles of the mud ship
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.70,0:09:22.14,IMEN,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}Sleeping in the white sand
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.47,0:09:28.50,IMEN,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}Oh, the little traveler
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.68,0:09:40.60,IMEN,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}Even we want be together
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.78,0:09:57.36,IMEN,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\blur5}we will be apart forever
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.41,0:09:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The mud whale is advancing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.25,0:09:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur5}Creatures are amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.71,0:09:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur5}Nobody has taught the star locusts,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.76,0:09:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur5}but they can flicker in the same rhythm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.22,0:09:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur5}The migratory birds know where to go since they were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.88,0:09:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur5}We are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.27,0:09:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur5}We have already known
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.02,0:09:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur5}how to move the mud whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.77,0:09:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They move the ship with such a game...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.90,0:09:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, that is this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.16,0:09:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How glory it is when all the residents gathered together.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.41,0:09:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Roharito-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.40,0:09:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.16,0:09:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.79,0:09:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The percentage of young is too high.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.67,0:09:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.60,0:09:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.34,0:09:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The dream is too strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.39,0:10:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you are nervous about the guests?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.93,0:10:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I also worry about what I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.69,0:10:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But the coming of guests,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.85,0:10:11.38,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(794,1000)}κόκαλο
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.85,0:10:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the understanding of Kókkalo after the dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.27,0:10:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,don't you think they mean we are connecting with somebody else?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.53,0:10:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We are really departing again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.18,0:10:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.87,0:10:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's something only the {\i1}Shirushi{\i0} know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.84,0:10:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,As a {\i1}Muin{\i0}, I feel a little lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.13,0:10:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we can go wherever we want with the mud whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.42,0:10:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Wherever...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.43,0:10:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Even where the empire's fang can't reach!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.02,0:10:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Was there a plague in the island?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.32,0:11:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the adults died when the empire attacked you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.49,0:11:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,As I told you before
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.58,0:11:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it's because Shirushi is short-lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.46,0:11:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, we seems to have too many young people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.33,0:11:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The soldiers of empire can use the same power as those on the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.59,0:11:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have never heard of other short-lived races.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.22,0:11:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you, the people of this island?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.26,0:11:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.76,0:11:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You hiding monkey! You just don't wanna tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.02,0:11:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I really don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.64,0:11:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If I know it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.68,0:11:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need to make these herbal medicine for prolonging life!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.99,0:11:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring me to your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.28,0:11:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.25,0:11:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Be quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.45,0:11:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I will show you the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.67,0:11:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the chart my ship used.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.03,0:12:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Cha...rt?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.26,0:12:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A map shows what the sea is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.30,0:12:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't understand a single...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.10,0:12:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys are really ignorant monkeys...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.39,0:12:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.52,0:12:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is the United Kingdom of Sidelasia where our Duchy of Amonlogia belongs to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.32,0:12:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,My ship was like this... crossed the sea of sand to the west.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.95,0:12:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we were swallowed into a strange torrent here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.53,0:12:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We were just about to wreck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.83,0:12:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Some days after we crossed that,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.87,0:12:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we landed this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.76,0:12:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mud whale is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.83,0:12:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey Suo! Return it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.54,0:12:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So the island without rudder was taken by the torrent,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.06,0:12:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and you were wandering in the same area for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.78,0:12:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.97,0:12:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a evil sea nobody has ever been.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.10,0:12:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But I crossed that dangerous area,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.98,0:12:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and found this island. What a great achievement!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.59,0:12:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.06,0:13:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We only know the ships of the empire
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.99,0:13:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,can cross the torrent with one's own will.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.61,0:13:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the mud whale with its rudder deprived
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.02,0:13:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,could go nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.08,0:13:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A bird in the cage...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.62,0:13:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This sea is a natural prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.21,0:13:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You were attacked by the biggest enemy of our country.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.09,0:13:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If you enter our bosom,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.13,0:13:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we can definitely protect you, small birds in cage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.58,0:13:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Roharito!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.90,0:13:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That country lies in the further west sea of sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.89,0:13:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a strange country with no name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.23,0:13:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No name?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.94,0:13:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.68,0:13:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But in that country, people don't have their real names.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.99,0:13:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This island is now heading for the Amonlogia in the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.07,0:13:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Since you now have the rudder, you should be able to break through this torrent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.00,0:13:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.38,0:14:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A brand new world is waiting for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.20,0:14:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the case? It's already so late.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.74,0:14:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I have something to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.54,0:14:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed it since the first sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.33,0:14:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Your skin has different color than those on the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.17,0:14:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You must... from that country.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.21,0:14:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your words? Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.72,0:14:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop looking up the people on the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.64,0:14:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.23,0:14:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop talking with them until we reach your country.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.35,0:15:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.28,0:15:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we accept a short-lived clans of unknown reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.69,0:15:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They may have some plague.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.95,0:15:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.20,0:15:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So you know the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.08,0:15:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.80,0:15:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Lykos?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.17,0:15:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't tell me what they are clearly,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.88,0:15:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't promise you to take their side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.88,0:15:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The cause is the mud whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.34,0:15:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mud whale...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.80,0:15:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean this ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.39,0:15:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason why this ship as well as the ships of empire can float on the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.85,0:15:44.04,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1268,995)}νοῦς
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.85,0:15:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is because a creature named Nous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.23,0:15:49.42,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(544,1000)}νοῦς
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.23,0:15:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Nous in my country eat the {\i1}emotions{\i0} of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.78,0:15:52.26,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1168,995)}sentikinesis
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.78,0:15:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and give them the power of {\i1}thymia{\i0} in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.84,0:15:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They are called the {\i1}Shirushi{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.95,0:15:59.76,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(630,1000)}νοῦς
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.95,0:15:59.76,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1106,1000)}φάλαινα
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.95,0:15:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But only the Nous on the island, Fallaina, has a different role.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.91,0:16:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Different role? What's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.44,0:16:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Lykos...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.96,0:16:06.29,GREEK11,,0,0,0,,{\pos(694,1000)}φάλαινα
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.96,0:16:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The food of Fallaina, and the source of Shirushi's thymia,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.75,0:16:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,which makes the island floating on the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.09,0:16:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is the {\i1}lives{\i0} of Shirushi living on the mud whale!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.85,0:16:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.90,0:16:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Chakuro!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.36,0:16:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Chakuro!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.78,0:16:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.49,0:16:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hearing the bitter truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.37,0:16:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and living without knowing the bitter truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.95,0:16:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter which you choose...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.79,0:16:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it some how.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.84,0:16:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But I pretended as I didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.75,0:16:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.10,0:16:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So I avoided it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.31,0:16:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Always...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.09,0:17:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Lykos.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.02,0:17:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We have made up our minds since you come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.86,0:17:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.98,0:17:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only thing we want to keep secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.57,0:17:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So the presbytery knows it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.08,0:17:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Suo, and everybody...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.46,0:17:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.98,0:17:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We will continue to support the Shirushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.13,0:17:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.58,0:17:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.00,0:17:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,After you get into the world outside, you will definitely notice it someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.17,0:17:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you just stay in the cage named Fallaina?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.64,0:17:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.06,0:17:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Start it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.11,0:17:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why these guys want to hole an assembly?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.78,0:17:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't the twins the bad eggs of the internal moles?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.45,0:18:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is made by the wings of birds shot with thymia!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.91,0:18:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a flag made for making an oath!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.50,0:18:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Under this flag, we will
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.57,0:18:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,form a new leader group, {\i1}the rudder of purple wing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.51,0:18:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is our rally!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.05,0:18:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We know we are not trusted by you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.76,0:18:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't expect everybody's agree here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.35,0:18:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But since you were born,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.19,0:18:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you did never doubt the system of this dolls world!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.90,0:18:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a puzzle for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.48,0:18:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We had been making troubles on the mud whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.11,0:18:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we couldn't blow the cobweb away!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.37,0:18:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you guys really believe
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the island is on a trip to the freedom?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.87,0:18:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It is said that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.12,0:18:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the mud whale is heading to the country of the guys landed recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.96,0:18:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Who decided that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.50,0:18:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not decided by you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.13,0:18:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.63,0:19:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The decisions of this island are made by the presbytery of Muin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.05,0:19:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.05,0:19:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Since long long before we were born!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.38,0:19:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And you think it's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.69,0:19:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.48,0:19:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll ask you another question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.56,0:19:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,During the recent war, how many Shirushi died?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.78,0:19:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I don't want to recall that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.62,0:19:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why you need to ask this now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.19,0:19:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There are so many died that you don't want to recall!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.78,0:19:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hakuji from the presbytery is the only Muin died in the attack from Skulax.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.87,0:19:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.21,0:19:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember the operation the presbytery raised that time!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.38,0:19:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They made trained Shirushi fight in the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.34,0:19:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And hide the Muin in the safe places of the mud whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.85,0:19:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.32,0:19:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The Muin without thymia is no help for the fights.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.25,0:19:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.93,0:19:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's even more difficult to fight while protecting the Muin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.19,0:19:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they would be the drags on us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.21,0:19:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.19,0:19:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Muin is exactly the drags on us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.23,0:20:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think it's cowardly?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.20,0:20:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They are unable to use thymia, they can't do anything themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.28,0:20:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They are pieces of shit who just have long lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.71,0:20:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Such guys set the operations for their own benefits,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.42,0:20:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and disposed of us Shirushi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.45,0:20:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we abandon that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.49,0:20:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you ever doubt it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.92,0:20:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You should know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.25,0:20:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The system of the mud whale itself is a rotten cheat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.21,0:20:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We will release us Shirushi from the dominance of Muin!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.86,0:20:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We Shirushi decide where we shall go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.73,0:20:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The ship should be ruled by us Shirushi,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.02,0:20:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,by the rudder of purple wing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.78,0:20:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thymia is the power driving the mud whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.41,0:20:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The strength of thymia decides where the mud whale go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.73,0:20:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Power is everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.41,0:20:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We rule the mud whale?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.28,0:20:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We go against the presbytery?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.50,0:20:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.92,0:20:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it! It is prohibited to use thymia in violence!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.95,0:21:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Isn't is a rule set by the Muin?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.51,0:21:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oni!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.39,0:21:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop the meaningless violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.78,0:21:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Even you become a dog of Muin?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.02,0:21:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm on nobody's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.57,0:21:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But you were the internal moles.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.20,0:21:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like you to be this crappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.03,0:21:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Crappy?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.49,0:21:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey what's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.43,0:21:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You run out of power? Together with your motivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.31,0:21:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Say it Oni, you take our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.72,0:21:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the most bloody devil in the island!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.06,0:22:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the strongest monster killed a number of enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.85,0:22:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.82,0:22:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We are strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.69,0:22:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We are different from Muin!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.82,0:22:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We have thymia!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.78,0:22:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,With this power,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.29,0:22:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody will insult us, trample us again!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.09,0:22:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.55,0:22:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.67,0:22:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Oni.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.33,0:22:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's show you the power of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.21,0:22:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We will live strongly and freely.
